Using Hojo Kanji (JISX0212, Supplementary Kanji) for pLaTeX2e     
                                                         by H. Kakugawa


hojo.pl, hojot.pl
- Template PL files for horizontal and vertical writing directionarities.

minh?.tfm, gothh?.tfm
- TFM files for Mincho and Gothic fonts, generated from 'hojo.pl'.

tminh?.tfm, tgothh?.tfm
- TFM files for Mincho and Gothic fonts, generated from 'hojot.pl'.

mkhojo.sh
- A shell script to generate TFM files from 'hojo.pl' and 'hojot.pl'.

jisx0212.sty
- A style file for using Hojo Kanji. Following commands are defined:
    * \begin{jisx0212} ...text... \end{jisx0212}
    * \HojoKanji{...text...}
  See 'sample.tex' for an example.

jy2mc.fd, jy2gt.fd, jt2mc.fd, jt2gt.fd
- Font definition files. (These files are used in 'jisx0208.sty'.)

sample.tex
- A sample document file to use Hojo Kanji.


See http://www.ascii.co.jp/pb/ptex/ for pLaTeX, a localized LaTeX2e system
for Japanese text.
